This paper deals with domain adaptation in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep learning framework, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of unlabeled target data and regularization techniques suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with feature alignment and distribution matching, which suggests that it may belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper reports results on object recognition tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
